REVIEW_TXT: We were having trouble finding a dog food for my dogs sensitive stomach. He used science diet and I wanted to try something else before buying that. A friend recommended purina one as their dog has a sensitive stomach and has no issues. We got a small bag and our dog loves the "lamb chop" pieces. It does not upset his stomach. We bought a cheap dog food to try and he was pooping 4x a day or more.. now he just poops once a day. Will be ordering again.
But they eat almost anything.  Vet sez it is best food.  I hope so as it costs a lot more than the 4 Health kibble I was getting at Tractor Supply.  Wife sez get it, I obey.

I have been feeding my GSD female Royal Canin ever since she was a pup and she has always done well on it.  But now, I'm going to switch her to a different brand because I simply can't afford to pay nearly $70 per month for dog food.  I know it's good food because our vet recommends it but there has to be another brand that's a bit cheaper that will work just as well for her.  My girl absolutely loves Rachel Ray's Roaster Dog Treats so I'm going to try her Nutrish dog kibble which is much more reasonably priced and has nutritious ingredients all made in the USA.  It pains me to do this but with grocery prices continuing to rise, I'm afraid it's time to make a change. Also, we always had GSDs growing up and we just fed them regular dog food...none of this expensive gourmet stuff...and they did fine...so I think the switch will be worth it!
My 4 year old mini Aussie does wonderfully on this kibble
NET_PROMOTER_COMMENT: Very good customer service- loads of choices

REVIEW_TITLE: Great product with a little work
REVIEW_TXT: It’s great. But, it’s a little shallow. 5 inch’s water depth. I put mine in a 55 gallon breeder tank. I cut out a plexiglass for the bottom and sides so that I could raise the depth to 6 inch’s. I use mine in a tank with firebelly newts. Since I made basically a plexiglass glass box it will be easily removed for cleaning. The space for the mister in the waterfall was a great idea too.

I was so impressed with the next day delivery on my two rabbit cages and guinea pig play yard.



I also appreciated the call I received when I had order two cages. One in the morning and one in late afternoon. The fact that you caught that and called to see if it may have been an error is so on the spot service.



I will be doing further business with "Chewy" and thank you so much.



Ginny
